<div class="container-white">
	<div class="container">	
		<div class="row">  
			<div class="span12">
				<h1>Character Traits &nbsp; <small><%= @student.name %></small></h1><br />
			</div>
			<div class="span8 offset2">
				
				<p>List 3 character traits you possess that an employer would value. The words that describe each trait should be adjectives.</p>

				<p>Capitalize words and punctuate as though your answers occur within the middle of a sentence. The tool will automatically capitalize the first word of every sentence or bullet. Be sure to proofread your documents.</p>

				<p><strong>Example:</strong> Because I am known to be <abbr title="Trait 1">kind</abbr>, <abbr title="Trait 2">enthusiastic</abbr>, and <abbr title="Trait 3">hard-working</abbr>, I believe I would be an asset to your company.</p>
		
				<form method="post">
					
					<p>
						<label for="trait_1">Trait 1</label>
						<input type="text" name="trait_1" id="trait_1" class="textfield span4" value="<%= @trait.trait_1 %>" />
					</p>
					<p>
						<label for="trait_2">Trait 2</label>
						<input type="text" name="trait_2" id="trait_2" class="textfield span4" value="<%= @trait.trait_2 %>" />
					</p>
					<p>
						<label for="trait_3">Trait 3</label>
						<input type="text" name="trait_3" id="trait_3" class="textfield span4" value="<%= @trait.trait_3 %>" />
					</p>
					
					<input class="btn btn-small btn-primary" type="submit" value="Save" /> &nbsp; <a class="btn btn-small" href="/student/resume/traits/traits">Cancel</a> &nbsp; <% if @student.traits.count > 0 %><a class="btn btn-small btn-warning" href="/student/resume/traits/<%= @trait.id %>/delete">Delete</a><% end %>
					
					</form>	
			</div>
			
		</div> <!-- /row -->
	</div> <!-- /container -->
</div> <!-- /container-white -->